name: Chick-fil-A
directions: At the entrance in line on the left. The wheelchair accessible bathroom is to the left & the family is to the right.
comment: You have to be a customer & both have keypads, so an employee has to let you in.

name: Avila Beach Pier
directions: Across the street from the Custom House (entered Custom House address because the pier doesn't have one), at the beginning of the pier
comment: Open to public, two unisex restrooms

name: IsoKristiina
directions: 2nd floor, inva wc

name: Starbucks
directions: Through the main doors to the right. 2 gender neutral bathrooms.

name: Kroger
directions: Left corner from entrance
comment: p clean, no issue, a little hidden, one stall, very large

name: Libertine Coffee Bar
directions: Far right side of entrance
comment: You have to be a paying customer

name: The Chopped Leaf
directions: At the back of restaurant. No key.
comment: Probably paying customers only, but it isn't locked or keyed.

name: Tim Hortons
directions: To the left of entrance. Same parking lot as Burger King and Super 8.
comment: Two gendered single stall plus accessible non-gendered single stall.

name: Microsoft Store - Fifth Avenue
directions: First floor on the left before the glass stairs, past the elevator & to the right.
comment: Two different single rooms with locking doors.

name: Ambition
directions: In the back on the left.
comment: Queer owned cafe. Two all gender washrooms.

name: The Pantry
directions: In the back to the right
comment: For customers only

name: Safeway
directions: Back of the store, aisle 10.
comment: Two non-gendered restrooms

name: Bombaj Tandoori
directions: When you enter the restaurant turn right. The restroom is there (as far as I remember there are stairs)
comment: If you're not a customer you have to pay 2 PLN. Just ask the staff.

name: Davis Centre extn
directions: From E3 to DC instead of taking the stairs, go behind the stairs. The door opens to an alley with the restrooms on the left.

name: Starbucks/Barnes & Nobles
directions: In the back of the Starbucks. It can be a little hard to notice, there's a decorative wall that obscures the door.
comment: This is a combo Barnes & Nobles + Starbucks, but the correct bathroom is in the Starbucks, not the Barnes & Nobles

name: Museum of Science and Industry
directions: gendered bathrooms (non single stall) are when you first walk in, however, if you go upstairs (only way to go when you get inside, i believe), there are two gender neutral single stall bathrooms near the food court.
comment: have to pay to get in

name: 112 Bolaro St, Dunedoo NSW 2844, Australia
directions: Near the side on the road
comment: Just walk in. It's clean and talks to you

name: Crab Cove
comment: Free to park guests

name: By Chloe
comment: Just act like you're looking at the menu

name: Einstein Brothers Bagels
comment: One bathroom is "Women" with two separate stalls inside. The other bathroom is a single that locks with a "Gender Neutral" sign.

name: Del Taco
directions: At the corner of E 20th St and Forest Ave. In the front door then turn left, straight back, past the front counter.
comment: I don't think you have to buy something first. the food there is great too. bathrooms are nice and clean.

name: Purple Park
directions: Typical park lavatories.

name: 321 Water st
directions: Behind the patio, in the workshop room

name: Oasis Falafel
directions: Past the register and pop machine on the right

name: Golden Corral
directions: Next to the rest of the bathrooms
comment: You have to be eating at the restaurant.

name: Natural Bridge Visitor Center
directions: First floor in the visitor center near park entrance
comment: Free to access

name: Central Library
directions: When you walk in, there is a hallway in between a conference room and stairs to the second floor. Go down that hallway and it is the first thing on your right

name: Fancy That
comment: The staff here have always been good w pronouns/name, doubt any problem should arise.

name: Bryan Kiefer Memorial Field
directions: If you walk towards the playground, it should be visible from there.
comment: It's a portapotty but it's clean and well taken care of.

name: Domini Canes
comment: You must be a paying customer. It is a restaurant.

name: Rapid City Regional Airport
directions: Between gates 1 and 3

name: Target
directions: It is located between the front entrances. It's a family restroom, and anyone can use it.
comment: You don't have to buy anything. No key is needed in my experience.

name: Target
directions: take a left just as you enter the store

name: HEB Grocery
directions: Second level (store level). Near checkout.
comment: Family restroom. Do not need to be a customer.

name: Enfield Public Library
directions: From the main entrance you turn left and there will be two unisex single stall restrooms. From the other entrance you go to the desk and they will be on your right. The first restroom, the one closer to the adult section, has a changing table.
comment: Act like you're looking around the library so it doesn't seem suspicious.

name: Pearl Street Library
directions: In the larger room in the back to the right there will be a doorway with a spiral staircase. You go down the stairs and at the end of the staircase to your left there is a unisex restroom.
comment: It is recommended that you ask the librarian about the restroom.

name: Himalaya Cuisine
directions: Far left of entrance, in back
comment: "Men's" and "Women's," but they're both single stall. You probably need to be a customer, but there is a small shop in addition to the restaurant.

name: The Satellite Room
directions: Go straight to the back. There are 4 restrooms.

name: Walker and Kraus, DDS
directions: Dentists office is I'm the back of the building. Left past the lobby, then left again.
comment: I assume they do not want non-patients coming in often to use the bathroom.

name: Starbucks
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms

name: Pigeon Point Lighthouse
directions: Next to the parking lot

name: La Chinita's Restaurant
directions: Near kitchen and enterance.

name: chesterfield towne center
directions: In food court they have a family restroom that has individual stalls
comment: full use for anyone, it's a mall so no restrictions

name: Positive Images
directions: Walk into the building and on the right is two doors, the further one is the entrance. Walk in and ask for a key to the bathroom. Usually there is a sign hung up blocking the gender signs, and even if there isn't, you can use either one.
comment: Positive Images is very trans friendly, there bathrooms are spacious single stalls, and you can use either one, no need to worry.

name: FIX Coffeebar
directions: In the back left
comment: Must be a paying customer

name: Milk and honey market
directions: Back to the left

name: Barista Parlor
directions: On the left from the front door

name: Herman's
directions: Through the front door, up the short set of stairs, through the glass door and to your left. The door is on the right side of the hallway.
comment: You could use this without paying. It seems to be a common restroom for the building.

name: Herman's
directions: In the front entrance, up the short set of stairs, through the double doors with glass windows, a little ways down the hallway to the left. The doorway is on the right and has a small common waiting area and 3 individual stalls.
comment: You could use it without being a customer, it seems like a common restroom for the building which contains a few businesses/ apartments.

name: Starbucks
directions: At back of the Starbucks
comment: Just walk in and use it, don't have to buy anything

name: Hyde Park Bar & Grille
directions: Once you enter from the front door restrooms are on the left of the bar. There are two handicap accessible, marked all gender restrooms.
comment: Probably need to be a paying customer.

name: Alamo Drafthouse Sloans Lake
directions: Immediately after the admission counter, first left.
comment: Either enter as a movie patron or request to use it polietly.

name: Carrigan Cafe
directions: Back left corner

name: The  Rook
comment: Super fun bar with board games!

name: Golden Triangle Mall
directions: Near the food court.
comment: Not in any particular store.

comment:
Borrego is a proud supporter of transgender equality and health care.
https://www.borregohealth.org/borrego-health-centro-medico-coachella-

name: Open community acupuncture
directions: Behind the building in the clinic
comment: Paying customers

name: Borrego Centro Medio Coachella
directions: In lobby
comment:
Borrego supports Transgender equality and provides health care to the Transgender community.
https://www.borregohealth.org/borrego-health-centro-medico-coachella-

name: Borrego Desert Hot Springs Community Health Center
directions: In lobby and in the patient staff back office

Borrego supports Transgender equality and provides bathroom safe spaces at this location.

comment:
Borrego is the leading provider of Transgender health care in the Coachella Valley.  We provide bathroom safe spaces for Transgender, Intersex, Gender Non-Conforming and Non-Binary.  
https://www.borregohealth.org/borrego-health-desert-oasis-womens-

name: DHS Specialty
directions: In the front lobby we have two gender neutral bathrooms
comment:
Borrego Specialty is the leading provider for Transgender, Intersex, Gender Non-Conforming and Non-Binary health care and has two gender neutral bathrooms at this location.  
https://www.borregohealth.org/borrego-health-specialty-care-center-

name: Centro Medico
directions: 11 different bathrooms all in this location. Two in front lobby.
comment:
11 different bathrooms.  Borrego Health Care Foundation has changed their signage and restroom space at this location to show their support for Transgender, Intersex, Gender Non-Conforming and Non-Binary people.
https://www.borregohealth.org/borrego-health-centro-medico-cathedral-

name: Centro Medico
directions: 11 different bathrooms all in this location. Two in front lobby.
comment: 11 different bathrooms.  Borrego Health Care Foundation has changed their signage and restroom space at this location to show their support for Transgender, Intersex, Gender Non-Conforming and Non-Binary people.

name: Aspen Pointe
directions: There are a variety of bathrooms here, the single room bathrooms are downstairs. Take the stairs or elevator then go down the open hallway. Go left and walk till you see the bathrooms on the left.
comment: Staff is trans friendly and the clients are diverse so shouldn't be a problem using any bathroom of your choice there. The single person ones are just a bit tucked away.

name: Jameson Brown Coffee Roasters
directions: Head left from the front door, restrooms in back area.
comment: Two unisex single restrooms. Also excellent coffee/drinks if you are so inclined.

name: Jameson Brown Coffee Roasters
directions: Left from front door, in back area.

name: Harp's Food Store
directions: From the entrance, turn left. It's to the left of the pharmacy, across from the toiletry aisles.

name: Putterz
directions: To the right once you enter. 2 locking unisex single occupancy restrooms.

name: Northwestern Department of Sociology
comment: Single user, all-gender restrooms on the 2nd floor of 1808 Chicago Ave, and on the 1st and 2nd floors of 1810 and 1812 Chicago Ave. Unfortunately no changing tables, but 1st floor 1810 Chicago restroom has quarter-operated machine for menstrual care supplies if needed.

name: Walmart
directions: It's at the back of the store, in a lobby across from the movies section. It's to the right of the gendered bathrooms.
comment: It's currently in the same lobby where you can pickup grocery orders. -6/29/17

name: Target
directions: It's near the entrance, next to a guest service counter. The door is at the entrance of a hall, before the gendered restrooms.
comment: It has a white door that isn't clearly marked. Look for a unisex sign on the wall.

name: Central Mall
directions: It's located in the food court, whose entrance is bordered by stone pillars. Look towards the curved half of the food court. It's located against the wall, in the center, between two gendered restrooms.
comment: It's a spacious family restroom, complete with a second mini toilet.

name: Harps Food Store
directions: After entering, walk left. It's on the left wall, near the pharmacy and across from the toiletry aisles.

name: Dwa Koty Cafe
directions: The door is on the right side of the bar; I don't think ordering anything should be necessary but you will probably have to ask someone about it.

name: California Lutheran university
directions: There's one in each residence hall

name: Mosaic Heath and Wellness/OakLawn
comment: Stern looks from the old lady's at the front desk, say nothing just follow the signs to down the hall to Mosaic. The front of the building is Oaklawn, the back is LGBT safe place Mosaic, and the staff of Mosaic are wonderful.

name: Sotto
directions: Down the stairs, to the left
comment: Probably should be a customer.

name: Chef's Chinese Food
directions: in the back by the host's table

name: Van Damme State Park
directions: Bathrooms by the showers are unisex / gender neutral & very clean.
comment: Must be camping at Van Damme

name: Foster's Freeze
directions: On the outside of the building. 2 unisex bathrooms. Nothing special, but relatively clean.
comment: Must be a customer, but no code required.

name: Eureka / Mid City Motor World
directions: Inside the Toyota service center by the front desk.

name: Missouri Botanical Gardens
directions: Two restrooms: One located in Spink Pavilion restroom area Second located in the Edward Jones Educational facility near the Brookings Center accessible from the Climatron, Children's garden entrance square, and Temperate House   (Note: Temperate House is not handicap accessible)
comment: Have to have a ticket to enter garden. Both labeled "family bathroom"
